A $\chi^2$ function was obtained in which the expectation value, for the observed number of counts, bin by bin, follows a Gamma distribution, as derived from the Bayes theorem. The $\chi^2$ function was then minimized, from where we extracted a new value for the $\lambda$ parameter, as reported below.


\section{A new limit on $\lambda$ and discussion of the results}\label{fitpar}
\label{fit results}
The result of the fit performed on the IGEX data is shown in figure \ref{fit}. The minimization gives for the free parameter of the fit the value $\alpha(\lambda) = 110 \pm 7$, corresponding to a reduced chi-square $\chi^2/n.d.f = 1.1$. 

\begin{figure}
\centering
\includegraphics[height=4in]{fit.png}
\caption{Fit of the X-ray emission spectrum measured by the IGEX experiment \cite{igex1,igex2}, using the theoretical fit function given by eqn. (\ref{fitfunc}).}\label{fit}
\end{figure}


